			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				Deris raises some good points.  And I agree about most of those things that we used to appreciate about EQ.
<br />

<br />
In EQ we definitely had much more of a sense of community than I have seen in WoW so far (granted the game is still young).  And I think there was a bit more quality over quantity.  In WoW there are just a lot more indistinct faces in the crowd, and it's a large crowd.
<br />

<br />
But there are tradeoffs.  Most of which I'm happy about in WoW.  EQ sucked for pvp (it was nothing more than an afterthought, I know, but it was stupidly frustrating and pointless trying to ever duel or pvp as a caster most of the time).  WoW player combat is something that overall I'm very pleased with.  It's not perfect and I'm not even going to get into the honor system, but I think it's fairly friendly in terms of being more effective with a wider level range and how useful classes are.
<br />

<br />
And also where in EQ it took me what, 2+ years to get to level 60, I can make that inside of 3 months in WoW without making myself miserable at times to do so.  It's a lot more friendly as far as time commitment goes.  EQ owned if you wanted to progress, especially in the high end.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
			</td></tr>
